# Walkthrough - Habit Count Accumulation

I have updated the application logic to allow habit counts to accumulate when you toggle habits on and off.

## Changes

### 1. Cumulative Habit Counting
- **File**: [src/App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx)
- **Change**: Modified the [toggleHabit](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx#925-949) function.
- **Behavior**:
    - Previously: Unchecking a habit reduced the total count by 1.
    - **Now**: Unchecking a habit **does not** change the total count.
    - **Result**: You can check a habit (+1), uncheck it (no change), and check it again (+1) to record multiple completions in a single day.

## Verification

### How to Verify
1.  **Build & Run**: Build the APK and install it on your device.
2.  **Check Status**: Note the current count of a habit in "Statistics" -> "Overall Status".
3.  **Toggle**:
    - Go to the Dashboard.
    - Click the habit to check it (Count increases by 1).
    - Click again to uncheck (Count stays same).
    - Click again to check (Count increases by 1).
4.  **Confirm**: Go back to "Statistics" and verify the count has increased by 2 (or more, depending on your clicks).

## Next Steps
- Please proceed with building the APK to test this on your device.
